---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<LegalLayout title="Terms of Service" description="The terms governing your use of the TrailNestCo website." path="/terms-of-service" updated="June 1, 2026">
  <p>
    These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of {SITE.domain} (the "Site"), operated
    by {SITE.business.legalName}. By using the Site, you agree to these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Use of content</h2>
  <p>
    Content on this Site, including articles, images, and graphics, is owned by {SITE.business.legalName}
    or its licensors and is protected by copyright. You may share links to our content but may not
    republish, scrape, or redistribute substantial portions without written permission.
  </p>

  <h2>No professional advice</h2>
  <p>
    Our reviews, guides, and recommendations are provided for general informational purposes only. They do
    not constitute professional, safety, or medical advice. Always follow manufacturer instructions and use
    appropriate judgment, training, and safety equipment when using outdoor or camping gear.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party links</h2>
  <p>
    The Site contains links to third-party websites, including affiliate and retailer links, which we do
    not control. We are not responsible for the content, products, or practices of any linked third-party
    site.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    The Site and its content are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. While
    we make reasonable efforts to keep information accurate and current (see our
    <a href="/fact-checking-policy">Fact-Checking Policy</a>), product specifications, pricing, and
    availability shown on the Site may change without notice.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, {SITE.business.legalName} shall not be liable for any indirect,
    incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Site or reliance on its content,
    including purchases made through links found on the Site.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to these Terms</h2>
  <p>We may revise these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, USA, without regard to conflict-of-law principles.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.business.legalName}<br />
    {SITE.business.addressFull}<br />
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.business.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.business.contactEmail}</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
